snippet: Detectives spent hours trying to determine how a three-foot-long bear that was spotted by a dog walker near 69th Street ended up in the park.
abstract: Baby black bear, a three-foot long female, is found dead off pathway on west side of Central Park; police describe the bear as having had trauma to her body, but it is not clear how she died; cub's body has been sent to state wildlife pathology unit in Albany to determine cause of death.

byline.original: By J. DAVID GOODMAN and DANIEL KRIEGER

lead_paragraph: Detectives spent hours trying to determine how a three-foot-long bear that was spotted by a dog walker near 69th Street ended up in the park.

headline.main: In a Mystery, a Baby Black Bear Is Found Dead in Central Park
headline.print_headline: In a Mystery, a Baby Black Bear Is Found Dead in Central Park
